62#define MSPIn(n) ((MSPI_Type*)(MSPI_BASE + (n * (MSPI_BASE - MSPI_BASE))))

64//
65// USE_CQ=1 will use the Command Queue in nonblocking transfers.
66// 0 uses plain DMA (w/o CQ) in nonblocking transfers.
67//
68#define MSPI_USE_CQ 1
69
70#define AM_HAL_MSPI_MAX_TRANS_SIZE 65535 // 2^16-1
71#define AM_HAL_MSPI_MAX_FIFO_SIZE 16
72#define AM_HAL_MSPI_DEFAULT_BURST_COUNT 32
73
74// Size guideline for allocation of application supplied buffers
75#define AM_HAL_MSPI_CQ_ENTRY_SIZE (18 * sizeof(uint32_t))
76#define AM_HAL_MSPI_HIPRIO_ENTRY_SIZE (6 * sizeof(uint32_t))

78#define AM_HAL_MSPI_SC_CLEAR(flag) ((flag) << 16)
79#define AM_HAL_MSPI_SC_SET(flag) ((flag))
80
82#define AM_HAL_MSPI_SC_UNPAUSE(flag) AM_HAL_MSPI_SC_SET(flag)
83#define AM_HAL_MSPI_SC_PAUSE(flag) AM_HAL_MSPI_SC_CLEAR(flag)
84
86#define AM_HAL_MSPI_SETCLR(module, scVal) \
87 do { \
88 MSPIn(module)->CQSETCLEAR = (scVal); \
89 } while (0);
90
92#define AM_HAL_MSPI_PAUSE_FLAG_RESV (MSPI_CQFLAGS_CQFLAGS_SWFLAG7 | MSPI_CQFLAGS_CQFLAGS_SWFLAG6 | MSPI_CQFLAGS_CQFLAGS_SWFLAG5)
93#define AM_HAL_MSPI_SC_RESV_MASK (AM_HAL_MSPI_PAUSE_FLAG_RESV | (AM_HAL_MSPI_PAUSE_FLAG_RESV << 8) | (AM_HAL_MSPI_PAUSE_FLAG_RESV << 16))
94
98#define AM_HAL_MSPI_PAUSE_FLAG_IDX (_VAL2FLD(MSPI_CQFLAGS_CQFLAGS, MSPI_CQFLAGS_CQFLAGS_CQIDX))
99#define AM_HAL_MSPI_PAUSE_FLAG_CQ (_VAL2FLD(MSPI_CQFLAGS_CQFLAGS, MSPI_CQFLAGS_CQFLAGS_SWFLAG7))
100#define AM_HAL_MSPI_PAUSE_FLAG_SEQLOOP (_VAL2FLD(MSPI_CQFLAGS_CQFLAGS, MSPI_CQFLAGS_CQFLAGS_SWFLAG6))
101#define AM_HAL_MSPI_PAUSE_FLAG_BLOCK (_VAL2FLD(MSPI_CQFLAGS_CQFLAGS, MSPI_CQFLAGS_CQFLAGS_SWFLAG5))
102
104#define AM_HAL_MSPI_PAUSE_DEFAULT (AM_HAL_MSPI_PAUSE_FLAG_IDX)
105#define AM_HAL_MSPI_CQP_PAUSE_DEFAULT (AM_HAL_MSPI_PAUSE_FLAG_IDX | AM_HAL_MSPI_PAUSE_FLAG_CQ)
